      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "Appeared after discussion with @patrickleet in gitter. \r\n\r\nIt is clear it should be a way to use custom code to modify config. For example based on docker/k8s/vault etc.secrets \r\n\r\nOriginally I was thinking of separate concept of config post processor \r\nbut actually it is likely that actual way developers will be using secrets is so deferent that it will be hard to build reusable post processors \r\n\r\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1HrC75oHWeQG-50JjglR1UkkuzV4JUaUyrpDiMtE7Wgk/edit#heading=h.un7ixe95bi7m\r\n\r\nso now it will be possible to just replace code in server.js from template declaration \r\n```\r\nlet gw = gateway()\r\n  .load(path.join(__dirname, 'configâ€™))\r\n// do whatever I want by direct access to gw.config\r\ngw.run()\r\n```",
